Here is the thin wrapper around the above **sub order_lineup()**.

```perl
my $H = [2, 6, 4, 5, 1, 3];
my $T = [1, 0, 2, 0, 1, 2];
my $O = order_lineup({ H => $H, T => $T });

print sprintf("\@H = (%s)\n", join(", ", @$H));
